    description_en: 'You made it here. 21 lessons. 21 days of learning, experimenting, and real change. Now it is time to consolidate everything into a single document: your Personal Sleep Blueprint.\n\nWhat your Blueprint includes:\n\n1. Your Chronotype (Lesson 2): Determines your ideal sleep window and energy peaks.\n\n2. Your Ideal Sleep Window: Based on your chronotype and life schedule, what is the sleep window that works best for you?\n\n3. Your Top 3 Protocols That Worked: Reviewing lessons 8-14, which 3 protocols made the biggest difference in your sleep quality? These are your non-negotiable foundations.\n\n4. Your Biggest Remaining Challenge: Be honest. What is the factor that still most harms your sleep? This is your next target.\n\n5. One Advanced Protocol to Try Next: Based on Acts 2 and 3, which technique have you not yet fully tried that could further elevate your sleep quality?\n\nHow to use your Blueprint:\n• Save this profile — you may want to share it\n• Use it to communicate your sleep needs to partners, family, and colleagues\n• Review it every 3 months — your profile will change as you improve\n\nYour achievement: You built awareness (Act 1), protocols (Act 2), and advanced optimization (Act 3). But the real achievement is simple: you decided sleep matters. That changes everything.',
